  "prompt": "My girlfriend and I took a break. About two months later she told me she made out with her ex during our break. What do I do?",
  "response": "Navigating a situation like this can be challenging and emotionally complex. Here are some steps you might consider taking:\n\n1. **Reflect on Your Feelings**: Take some time to process how you feel about the situation. Are you hurt, betrayed, confused? Understanding your emotions can help you communicate better.\n\n2. **Communicate Openly**: When you're ready, have an open and honest conversation with your girlfriend. Express how her actions made you feel and listen to her perspective as well. Understanding each other's thoughts and feelings can be crucial.\n\n3. **Consider the Context of Your Break**: Breaks can mean different things to different people. Discuss what the break meant for both of you and expectations during that time. This can provide clarity on why she made that choice.\n\n4. **Assess the Relationship**: Think about whether you see a future with her and if you can move past this incident. Trust and communication are key components of a strong relationship. Consider whether those can be rebuilt.\n\n5. **Set Boundaries**: If you decide to continue the relationship, discuss and agree on boundaries to avoid similar misunderstandings in the future.\n\n6. **Seek Support**: Talk to friends, family, or even a professional who can provide support and perspective as you navigate this situation.\n\n7. **Take Your Time**: Don't rush into any decisions. It's okay to take time to think about what you really want and what is best for you.\n\nUltimately, trust your instincts about what's right for you and your relationship.",
